
-- Database = container for all the data you store;

-- Database Dictionary = a comprehensive list of the structure and types of
--  data in the database;

-- Table = collection of related data held in the database;

-- Field/column = basic (individual) unit of data in a table;

-- Row/record = a single set of data containing all the columns
--  in the table;

-- Flat File database = database that stores all data in a single table
--  (results in duplication);

-- Database Normalization = splitting the table data in relational
--  tables to avoid duplication;

-- View = a selection of rows and columns, possible from more than
--  one table;

